# Subscription Prices in 2026

:::nota
Breaking news — April 9, 2026. OpenAI announces a new Pro tier at USD 100/month for ChatGPT, offering 5x more Codex usage than Plus and full access to the Pro model. The USD 200/month plan remains the ceiling. This reshapes the accessibility landscape. Reference exchange rate: 1 USD = S/ 3.389.
:::

| Platform / Plan | USD/mo. | In S/ | What it includes |
| :--- | ---: | ---: | :--- |
| ChatGPT Plus | $20 | S/ 67.78 | Full GPT-4o, DALL-E, reasoning, 10 Deep Research/mo. |
| ChatGPT Pro (NEW) | $100 | S/ 338.90 | 5x Codex vs Plus, exclusive Pro model, unlimited Instant & Thinking |
| ChatGPT Pro (max) | $200 | S/ 677.80 | Fully unlimited, o1 Pro mode, absolute priority |
| Claude Pro | $20 | S/ 67.78 | Claude Code, code execution, unlimited projects, MCP |
| Claude Max 5x | $100 | S/ 338.90 | 5x Pro limits, Opus access, priority |
| Claude Max 20x | $200 | S/ 677.80 | 20x Pro limits, full Opus access |
: Subscription prices in 2026 {#tbl:subscription-prices}

Both platforms now have three clear tiers: USD 20 basic, USD 100 intermediate/pro, and USD 200 maximum. The price alignment between ChatGPT and Claude across these tiers reveals a symmetric price war.

# Real Cost with Taxes by Country

The prices of USD 20, USD 100, and USD 200 are pre-tax. Each country applies its own VAT, IGV, or GST to digital services. The tables below show the real cost of the basic, intermediate, and maximum plans with taxes included.

:::nota
Key figure for Peru. With an 18% IGV, the basic USD 20 plan actually costs USD 23.60 (S/ 79.98) and the maximum USD 200 plan reaches USD 236 (S/ 799.80). The maximum plan with taxes equals 70.8% of Peru's minimum wage.
:::

